'''''G.Nius''''' is a 1988 French [[action game|action video game]] developed by [[Lankhor]] for [[Amiga]] and [[Atari ST]].

== Plot ==
The player is a robot named G.Nius who has crash-landed his spaceship. He needs to escape the ship before it vaporizes by visiting every room to turn off a switch.

== Development ==
The game experienced significant distribution problems. The game was prevented from being sold in parts of France.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lankhor.net:80/jeux/jeux.php3?jeu=8&menu=presentation|title=Lankhor.net|date=2002-04-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20020429042248/http://www.lankhor.net/jeux/jeux.php3?jeu=8&menu=presentation|access-date=2018-03-13|archive-date=2002-04-29|url-status=live}}</ref>

== Reception ==
''The Games Machine'' felt the game could be annoying and confusing at times.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/the-games-machine-21|title=The Games Machine Issue 21}}</ref> ''ACE'' magazine praised the frenetic, zany action, as well as the aesthetics.<ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://archive.org/details/ace-magazine-19/page/n55/mode/2up |journal=ACE |issue=19|date=April 1989 |page=56 |last1=Jarratt |first1=Steve |title=Screen Test: G.NIUS}}</ref>

